    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Sooji Halwa (Semolina Pudding) is a classic Indian sweet dish made with roasted semolina, ghee, sugar, and flavored with cardamom. It‚Äôs quick, delicious, and commonly made during festivals or pooja.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>20 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup sooji (semolina)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup ghee (clarified butter)</li>
        <li>1 cup sugar</li>
        <li>2.5 cups water</li>
        <li>1/4 tsp cardamom powder</li>
        <li>Chopped dry fruits (cashews, almonds, raisins)</li>
        <li>Few saffron strands (optional)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Boil water in a pan, add sugar, saffron (optional), and keep it hot.</li>
        <li>In a separate pan, heat ghee and roast the sooji on medium heat until golden and aromatic.</li>
        <li>Carefully add the hot sugar water to the roasted sooji, stirring continuously to avoid lumps.</li>
        <li>Add cardamom powder and cook until mixture thickens and ghee starts separating.</li>
        <li>Garnish with fried cashews, almonds, and raisins. Serve hot.</li>
    </ol>
